RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Claiming Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR. COWBOY BRADLEY took a quick lead and rated the pace inside, widened at the rail on the far turn, was kept alert through the upper stretch then taken in hand later yards. TAKE AIM stalked off the rail, challenged approaching the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and settled for second best. ASK HIM OAKEY hopped at the start and raced off the rail the first turn, picked up the chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn then flattened in the lane. ROBBEDINTHEBAHAMAS settled just off the pace about the three path, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the three path and showed little in the lane. ARTHUR S GOLD started bucking shortly after the start, regained control and dropped well back from contention and could only improve position. STRONG CURLIN showed little response. COLONEL CAPPY steadied at the start then stalked the early pace, dropped back approaching the three eighths pole, showed no response and was eased from the mid point of the far turn then collapsed post race and had to be vanned off.

ENTRY.NAME: Mr. Cowboy Bradley
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,asked nearing 1/4,widen,kept alert,in hand late

ENTRY.NAME: Take Aim
ENTRY.OWNER: Jones Jr Michael E and JKX Racing
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail,challenged 3/8,off rail turn,settled 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Colonel Cappy
ENTRY.COMMENT: steadied start,stalked off rail,eased,collapsed post race

ENTRY.NAME: Robbedinthebahamas
ENTRY.COMMENT: just off pace 3p,chased 3/8,3p far turn,empty lane

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SISTER'S DUTY took the lead past the half mile pole and rated the pace, was urged clear at the rail midway on the turn and held well under steady stretch handling. FORTES chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn near the rail and dueled for second mid-stretch. GARY DOING BIZ gave chase past the half mile pole but dropped back off the rail midway on the turn and relented second mid-stretch. KOBE'S GIRL gave chase outside, raced in the five path on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. CAPTAIN SAM broke a step slow and steadied at the start, raced in the four path on the turn and was eased the final sixteenth. REAWAKENED gave only briefly close chase then faded past the three eighths pole.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 60. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. RACE.FOOTNOTES: PURE NONSENSE pressured the pace from the three eighths pole and dueled at even terms from that point, contested the edge at the rail on the turn and dug in determinedly to hold off ELLIES AT WINDSOR through the stretch. The latter rated a slim early lead then set a pressured pace leaving the three eighths pole, contested at a close disadvantage two deep on the turn and finished well at the outside flank of the winner. LET'S DO THIS gave chase, raced at the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. AWESOME MOON was unprepared for the break then gave chase leaving the chute, raced off the rail on the turn and finished well to pass rivals. POWER SONDE gave chase, raced near the rail on the turn then flattened stride. COWGIRL ATTITUDE chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn in the three path and ran evenly in the stretch. LIVANA chased through the backstretch, raced close in the four path on the turn then weakened in the lane. CAT WITH A NOTION was not a factor and rounded the turn about the six path.

ENTRY.NAME: Pure Nonsense
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace,dueled even terms,edge rail turn,determinedly

ENTRY.NAME: Awesome Moon
ENTRY.COMMENT: unprepared break,chased leaving chute,off rail turn,finished well

HELLUVA LADY raced four wide on the first turn, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole but weakened in the three path of the far turn. WATERLOO ROSE raced off the rail on the first turn and never factored.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MACHEN'S RIDGE saved ground, bid nearing the three eighths pole and rounded the far turn in the three path, drifted to the five path into the lane, dug in for the lead later yards and raced clear toward the wire. LEG UP stalked three wide, bid nearing the three eighths pole and loomed a close factor three wide on the far turn, dueled to a slim brief lead mid-stretch but was outfinished in later yards. CHASE LIL ME saved ground racing well back from early contention, eased out into the backstretch and started a bid toward the seven sixteenths pole, steadily improved in the seven path of the far turn and finished well to take third the final yards. DON'TCALLTOOEARLY saved ground, eased out with a bid toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the three path and passed some rivals. GET OFF MY CLOUD moved to the inside and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole, was met a the rail passing the quarter pole, contested even terms on the far turn then weakened the final sixteenth. S S SPARTAN ENERGY raced in the six path the first turn, saved some ground on the second turn and bid mildly leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path and weakened in the lane. CHESAPEAKE CHARLIE angled to the five path on the first turn and settled off the pace from the seven eighths pole, raced in the three path of the far turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and weakened in the lane.
